sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: A scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Scar site created by A part ligation. Used for entering composite parts on the Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Horwitz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K106002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence for the Sir2 gene with AB ends for Aar1 cloning. Sir2 is a HDAC that we use for silencing in our project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Quan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since this is an AB part, there is a ATG but no stop codon. For more information on AarI cloning, please refer to the UCSF 2008 igem page.
